

           Title: Dance School Application Development

⦁	Introduction
Bharatanatyam is one of the oldest classical dance forms of India, known for its expressive storytelling, rhythm, and discipline. Traditionally, Bharatanatyam is taught in physical classrooms where students rely heavily on in-person guidance, handwritten notes, and memory-based practice.
However, with the advancement of technology, there is a growing need to digitize traditional teaching systems to improve accessibility, organization, and efficiency. The Padanaad Dance Studio application is designed as a modern solution that integrates technology with classical dance education.
This mobile application provides a centralized platform where teachers can manage learning content, track attendance, monitor student performance, and communicate effectively with students and parents. Students can access learning materials anytime, while parents can monitor their child's progress and fee payments.
The system bridges the gap between traditional teaching and modern digital solutions, ensuring a structured and efficient learning environment.

⦁	Problem Statement
The traditional Bharatanatyam teaching system faces several limitations:
Firstly, attendance tracking is usually done manually using registers, which can lead to errors, misplacement of records, and difficulty in maintaining historical data.
Secondly, students often lack continuous access to learning materials such as practice videos, theory notes, and session summaries. This limits their ability to revise and practice outside class hours.
Thirdly, communication between teacher, students, and parents is unstructured and often happens through informal channels, leading to missed updates and confusion.
Additionally, fee management is handled manually, making it difficult to track payments, pending dues, and generate proper receipts.
Another major issue is the absence of a centralized system to monitor student progress and performance over time.
These challenges create inefficiencies and reduce the overall quality of the learning experience.

⦁	Objective
The main objectives of this project are:
⦁	To digitize the Bharatanatyam learning process
⦁	To provide structured access to educational content
⦁	To simplify attendance and performance tracking
⦁	To improve communication among users
⦁	To ensure transparent fee management
⦁	To create a user-friendly and efficient mobile application

⦁	Scope of the Project
The scope of this project includes the design and development of a mobile application that addresses the above problems by providing a digital platform for Bharatanatyam learning.
The application supports three main user roles:
⦁	Teacher: Manages content, attendance, fees, and communication
⦁	Student: Accesses learning materials and tracks performance
⦁	Parent: Monitors child’s progress and handles payments

The system includes the following features:
⦁	Content Management (videos, notes, summaries)
⦁	Attendance Tracking System
⦁	Fee Management and Payment Tracking
⦁	Unified Communication System
⦁	Profile Management
⦁	Dashboard-based navigation
The application is designed specifically for mobile devices and can be used by dance institutes, individual instructors, and learners.


⦁	Methodology
The development of the Padanaad Dance Studio application follows a structured and systematic software development approach. The methodology ensures that the application is designed, developed, and deployed efficiently while meeting user requirements.
 
5.1 Requirement Analysis
In this phase, the requirements of all stakeholders are identified and analyzed. 
The system considers three main user roles:
⦁	Teacher
⦁	Student
⦁	Parent

Each user has specific needs:
⦁	Teachers manage content, attendance, fees, and communication
⦁	Students access learning materials and track attendance
⦁	Parents monitor progress and manage payments
This phase ensures that the system addresses real-world problems effectively.

5.2 System Design
The system design phase involves planning the structure and user interface of the application.
UI/UX design is created using Figma
Mobile-first design approach is followed
Navigation flow is defined (Splash → Login → Dashboard → Features)
Role-based dashboards are designed
This ensures a clean, user-friendly, and intuitive interface.

5.3 System Development
In this phase, the application is developed using modern technologies.
⦁	Frontend is developed using React Native
⦁	Expo is used for development and testing
⦁	Component-based architecture is implemented Modules developed include:
⦁	Authentication system
⦁	Dashboard
⦁	Content management
⦁	Attendance system
⦁	Fee tracking
⦁	Communication system
Each module is integrated to form a complete application.
          5.4 Testing
Testing is performed to ensure system reliability and functionality. Types of testing include:
⦁	Functional Testing – checks all features
⦁	UI Testing – ensures proper design and responsiveness
⦁	Integration Testing – ensures modules work together
⦁	User Testing – checks usability
Errors are identified and resolved during this phase.

5.5 Deployment
After testing, the application is deployed.
⦁	Application is run using Expo
⦁	APK is generated using EAS Build
⦁	App is installed on Android devices
This makes the application ready for use.

5.6 Maintenance and Future Improvements
After deployment, the system is maintained and improved based on user feedback. Future enhancements may include:
⦁	Push notifications
⦁	Live class integration
⦁	AI-based performance analysis
⦁	Advanced payment features
Continuous updates ensure better performance and user experience.

